Since the tarball at metalab didn't compile out of the box on linux 2.2
glibc2 platforms, I did a couple of tweaks in the case you know ada but
don't know basic C .. which could be possible since I have no clue on ada :)

If you are compiling under linux, just type make.  No need to edit config.h
Also, have a look to the README.ancient file.  If you run into problems, you
can email me at <ragnar@lightside.ddns.org> or <ragnar@redestb.es>

Disclaimer:
This version isn't released by the New York University.  I tried contacting
them with no luck, so I'm bumping version up to 1.12  If you happen to know
how to get in touch with the original developers, please let me know.

